      <!-- ===== FEATURED CASE STUDY ===== -->
      <section class="block" id="case-study">
        <div class="num-tag reveal"><b>04</b> featured case study</div>
        <h2 class="block-title reveal">Turning an inherited codebase into a secure, documented API platform</h2>
        <p class="block-lede reveal">At Apollo Solutions, I was handed a fintech backend built by a third-party
          development company — functional, but not built to last. Here's the path from audit to a hardened API layer.
        </p>

        <div class="phase-list">
          <div class="phase-item reveal">
            <div class="phase-num">01</div>
            <div class="phase-content">
              <h3>Audited the inherited codebase</h3>
              <p>Reviewed the existing implementation end to end and wrote a formal findings report identifying where it
                broke clean code principles and where it diverged from Odoo's own ORM, module, and design methodology —
                the specific misuses, not just general complaints.</p>
              <span class="phase-skill">Code review &amp; technical auditing</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-item reveal">
            <div class="phase-num">02</div>
            <div class="phase-content">
              <h3>Documented the target architecture</h3>
              <p>Turned the audit into a proposal: what the solution should look like, and the sequence the refactor
                should follow so the platform stayed shippable while it was being rebuilt underneath.</p>
              <span class="phase-skill">Technical documentation &amp; proposal writing</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-item reveal">
            <div class="phase-num">03</div>
            <div class="phase-content">
              <h3>Built a REST API framework on top of Odoo's HTTP layer</h3>
              <p>Replaced ad hoc endpoints with a reusable framework — a single, consistent foundation for every API the
                platform would need going forward.</p>
              <span class="phase-skill">API architecture</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-item reveal">
            <div class="phase-num">04</div>
            <div class="phase-content">
              <h3>Integrated OpenAPI/Swagger documentation</h3>
              <p>Wired the framework to generate accurate, always-current API documentation, replacing tribal knowledge
                with a spec that other developers and integration partners could actually read.</p>
              <span class="phase-skill">API documentation standards</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-item reveal">
            <div class="phase-num">05</div>
            <div class="phase-content">
              <h3>Added group-based access control to every documented endpoint</h3>
              <p>Restricted visibility by user group — a payment gateway client can see and call only the endpoints
                relevant to it, with mobile-only endpoints walled off entirely. Least-privilege access, enforced at the
                API layer, not left to convention.</p>
              <span class="phase-skill">Access control &amp; least-privilege design</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-item reveal">
            <div class="phase-num">06</div>
            <div class="phase-content">
              <h3>Unified endpoints under API grouping</h3>
              <p>Grouped endpoints so authentication and method configuration are set once per group instead of per file
                — meaning protection and tracking layers can be added platform-wide in one place, and the codebase is
                now structured to drop in an anti-fraud layer without a rewrite.</p>
              <span class="phase-skill">Framework design for extensibility</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-item reveal">
            <div class="phase-num">07</div>
            <div class="phase-content">
              <h3>Built a JWT authentication module for mobile endpoints</h3>
              <p>Gave the mobile app its own token-based authentication path, decoupled from the web session model the
                legacy code relied on.</p>
              <span class="phase-skill">JWT authentication</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-item reveal">
            <div class="phase-num">08</div>
            <div class="phase-content">
              <h3>Designed a generic OTP engine</h3>
              <p>Built once, used twice: the same OTP engine authenticates a user by phone number and approves sensitive
                operations — like a payment — so every new "verify this action" requirement reuses the same audited code
                path instead of a new one-off implementation.</p>
              <span class="phase-skill">Reusable security infrastructure</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="upgrade-note reveal">
          <span class="sg-label">Also part of this rebuild</span>
          <p>This overhaul ran alongside a full platform upgrade — carrying business logic across multiple major Odoo
            version boundaries (from an older 15.x base up to 17/18) without breaking live financial workflows in the
            process. Version upgrades are where inherited technical debt usually surfaces first, which is what made the
            earlier audit worth doing properly.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

